I learned more calculus and how to take better initiative of my learning.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The strengths were the office hours offered. The course could be improved if the practice materials given before the midterm were tailored towards the actual exam.

My strengths are figuring out the work and working hard to understand the material. My biggest weakness is trying to confirm to myself that I really know the work and I am really prepared for an exam. This can be overcome by having myself do extra practice problems to really make sure my knowlodge is at the level I want it to be.
workshops were really helpful. no particular weaknesses

The strengths are that we learned a lot through the professors and TA in this course.
There aren't any weaknesses.

Strengths- very engaging, good Task
Weaknesses- sometimes the instructors delayed to give feedback

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this course because it taught me how to take initiative of my learning at Yale and how to get help when I am struggling with understanding the material.

I would only recommend this course to someone if they haven't taken calculus before and needed it for their major. This course is a lot annoying work and unless someone really needs it, I wouldn't recommend the course to them.
yes. it enables one to clearly understand the concepts of integration.
